<BaseLayout title="About Sanjay Gupta" description="Sanjay Gupta is a former Managing Director in investment banking with over 20 years of experience across M&A, capital markets, and restructuring.">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">About the Author</h1>
    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <p>Sanjay Gupta is a former Managing Director in investment banking with over two decades of experience at bulge bracket and elite boutique firms. His career has spanned M&A advisory, capital markets, restructuring, and fund formation across multiple market cycles.</p>
      <p>After leaving the sell-side, Sanjay founded Swiss Finance Institute to bridge the gap between what aspiring bankers read online and what actually happens on the desk. The content on this site reflects real experience - not regurgitated interview prep or career coach marketing.</p>
      <h2>Credentials</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Former Managing Director, Investment Banking</li>
        <li>20+ years across M&A, ECM, DCM, and Restructuring</li>
        <li>Registered Investment Adviser (Connecticut)</li>
        <li>Series 7, 63, 79 licensed</li>
        <li>MBA, Finance</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>Philosophy</h2>
      <p>Most investment banking content online falls into two categories: oversimplified career advice from people who never worked on a deal, or overly technical content that misses the human element. This site aims for neither. Every article is written from the perspective of someone who has actually sat in the chair, pulled the all-nighters, and navigated the politics.</p>
      <p>The goal is simple: give you the information you need to make smart decisions about your career in finance, delivered without the fluff.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
